Commentary: direct hit from Shenwari and Shakib is gone! Oh this is disastrous for Bangladesh. Poor judgement from Shakib. Got back to a googly, flicked it to Shenwari's left at midwicket and just took off without a call. Mushfiqur saw no run there and he stood his ground. Shakib slipped as he looked to turn when he realised this and was nowhere in the picture as this throw came in one the bounce to take out the stumps. Mushfiqur had taken a couple of steps down, but it doesn't appear that either of them had made a call
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT

Commentary: looks like Mushfiqur could be run out at the non-striker's end! It hinges on whether Rashid knocked the stumps out with his hips...looks like the tricep and elbow area on slow-mo replay. He has the ball in his hand so this will go his way! Mushfiqur Rahim is gone. Rashid picked up the throw from the leg side in front of the stumps and was falling backwards as he collected the throw and looked to take out the stumps. As a result there was some element of him falling onto the stumps but in the end it is all clean. The hip was nowhere close to the stumps. But once again, atrocious running. Kayes had blocked this googly into the square leg region. He didn't want the run. Mushfiq was past halfway because he wanted it. Had no chance of making it back. Once again, no calling.
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Imrul Kayes, OUT
